    "description": "Role Summary: The Senior Python Developer will lead software development efforts using expert knowledge of Python and related technologies. Collaboration with cross-functional teams is essential for successful project delivery. Experience in Agile methodologies preferred but not required due to onboarding plans aligning senior developers directly into the team after their skills acquisition phase, which typically spans 12 months within this role's timeframe and budget constraints of our current projects dictate a focus more towards immediate skill-building.\r\nKey Responsibilities: - Develop scalable Python applications leveraging Django framework knowledge for efficient cloud deployment on AWS infrastructure.\r\n- Design, implement, test using PostgreSQL databases ensuring high performance, and data integrity within the application environment.\r\n- Collaborate with cross-functional teams to define requirements clearly, gather feedback promptly, iterate quickly through Agile sprints for rapid prototyping of features.\r\nRequired Qualifications: - A Bachelor's or Master's degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, Software Engineering, or related field is required as a foundation knowledge necessary for this position.\r\n- Strong experience and demonstrated proficiency with Python programming language along with expertise in Django web framework development within an Agile environment are essential qualifications to ensure seamless integration into our workflows right away.\r\n- A proven track record of working on complex, large-scale software projects is necessary due to the significant role this position plays as a team leader and primary developer for major project contributions across various phases from conception through deployment within AWS cloud infrastructure leveraging PostgreSQL databases effectively in Python applications development contexts here at TechForward Solutions.",
